<p>The regular icosahedron is a Platonic solid. Edge length and radius have=
 the same unit (e.g. meter), the area has this unit squared (e.g. square me=
ter), the volume has this unit to the power of three (e.g. cubic meter). A/=
V has this unit <sup>-1</sup>.</p>
<br><br>
<img src=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/img/net/icosahedron.png" width=3D"3=
00" height=3D"147" alt=3D"Net of a icosahedron"><br>
Net of an icosahedron, the three-dimensional body is unfolded in two dimens=
ions.<br><br>
<p>A regular icosahedron is point-symmetrical to its center. It has 15 plan=
es of symmetry and is rotationally symmetrical to a total of 31 axes of rot=
ation. The dual body of the icosahedron is the <a href=3D"https://rechneron=
line.de/pi/dodecahedron.php">dodecahedron</a>, of which the icosahedron is =
the dual body itself. In the icosahedron, five triangles meet at one point,=
 in the dodecahedron, three pentagons meet. If you regularly cut off the co=
rners of an icosahedron, you get the Archimedean solid <a href=3D"https://r=
echneronline.de/pi/truncated-icosahedron.php">truncated icosahedron</a>. Th=
e intersection of an icosahedron and a dodecahedron is a <a href=3D"https:/=
/rechneronline.de/pi/truncated-dodecahedron.php">truncated dodecahedron</a>=
. If you place matching <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/tetrahedron.=
php">regular tetrahedra</a> on the side surfaces, you get a <a href=3D"http=
s://rechneronline.de/pi/great-stellated-dodecahedron.php">great stellated d=
odecahedron</a>, the last of the four regular star polyhedra. The icosahedr=
on is the "roundest" of all regular polyhedra, it has the largest volume pe=
r diameter and the flattest corners.</p>
<p>Icosahedrons are used as twenty-sided dice. Some viruses are icosahedral=
-shaped, including the rhinovirus, which is responsible for the common cold=
, but also the dangerous hepatitis B virus and poliovirus.</p>
